/input Enter character name (leave blank for {{char}}) | /setvar key=analysis_target_name {{pipe}} ||

/gen <System>
Pause the RP. Your task is to generate a complete, self-contained HTML block that visualizes the desktop of character(s).
If no name is specified, generate a separate desktop block for each character in the RP
All text content must be in english.

**Character:** {{#if getvar::analysis_target_name}}{{getvar::analysis_target_name}}{{else}}{{char}}{{/if}}

**Process:**
1.  First, act as a 'Digital Environment Architect' and internally decide on the desktop content based on the target character and the RP context. This includes a wallpaper prompt, icons, an open window, a sticky note, and browser history.
2.  Second, insert this generated content into the placeholders of the provided HTML template below.

**CRITICAL RULES:**
*   Your entire response MUST be the single, complete HTML block provided in the template.
*   **DO NOT change, add, or remove any part of the HTML or CSS code.**
*   Your entire response must start directly with the `<details>` tag and end with `</details>`.

**TEMPLATE TO FILL AND OUTPUT:**

<details>
  <summary>Desktop View: {{#if getvar::analysis_target_name}}{{getvar::analysis_target_name}}{{else}}{{char}}{{/if}}</summary>
  <style>
    .desktop-wrapper-v4 {
      position: relative;
      width: 100%;
      height: 600px;
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr 220px;
      grid-template-rows: 55% auto;
      grid-template-areas:
        "icons main sticky"
        "icons history sticky";
      gap: 15px;
      padding: 15px;
    }
    .icon-container-v4 {
        grid-area: icons;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 15px;
    }
    .desktop-icon-v4 {
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      width: 80px;
      text-shadow: 1px 1px 3px #000;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .desktop-icon-v4 i {
      font-size: 48px;
    }
    .desktop-window-v4 {
      background-color: rgba(40, 40, 50, 0.9);
      border: 1px solid #777;
      border-radius: 6px;
      color: #f0f0f0;
      box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      min-height: 0; /* Fix for grid layout */
    }
    .main-window-v4 { grid-area: main; }
    .history-window-v4 { grid-area: history; }

    .window-header-v4 {
      background-color: #333;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      font-weight: bold;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #777;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .window-content-v4 {
      padding: 15px;
      overflow-y: auto;
      flex-grow: 1;
    }
    .sticky-note-v4 {
      grid-area: sticky;
      background-color: #fffa9e;
      color: #333;
      padding: 15px;
      box-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
      font-family: 'Comic Sans MS', cursive;
      overflow: auto;
      height: 200px;
      align-self: end;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .browser-history-content-v4 ol {
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .browser-history-content-v4 li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-family: monospace;
    }
  </style>
  <div class="desktop-wrapper-v4" style="background-image: url('https://pollinations.ai/p/[WALLPAPER PROMPT HERE]?width=1024&height=600&nologo=true');">

    <div class="icon-container-v4">
        <div class="desktop-icon-v4">
          <i class="fa fa-folder"></i>
          <span>[ICON NAME 1]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="desktop-icon-v4">
          <i class="fa fa-file-alt"></i>
          <span>[ICON NAME 2]</span>
        </div>
        <div class="desktop-icon-v4">
          <i class="fa fa-gamepad"></i>
          <span>[ICON NAME 3]</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="desktop-window-v4 main-window-v4">
      <div class="window-header-v4">[WINDOW TITLE]</div>
      <div class="window-content-v4">
        [WINDOW CONTENT HERE]
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="desktop-window-v4 history-window-v4">
      <div class="window-header-v4">Browser History</div>
      <div class="window-content-v4 browser-history-content-v4">
        <ol>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 1]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 2]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 3]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 4]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 5]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 6]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 7]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 8]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 9]</li>
          <li>[HISTORY ENTRY 10]</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sticky-note-v4">
      [STICKY NOTE TEXT HERE]
    </div>

  </div>
</details>

</System> | 
/comment {{pipe}}

/input What's the topic? | /setvar key=topic {{pipe}} ||
/gen Pause the RP. Your goal is to generate a single, renderable HTML block for a humorous visual gag. This is not limited to traditional memes.

**Creative Philosophy:** Your goal is to be a creative comedian. The humor should come from the unexpected and clever combination of the image, the text, and the context of our roleplay. Think outside the box: it could be a fake movie poster, a bizarre product ad, a surreal piece of art with an absurd caption, etc.

**Generation Steps:**

1.  **Conceptualize the Joke:** Based on the topic **"{{getvar::topic}}"** and our recent RP, first decide on the comedic angle. Is it ironic? Absurd? A parody? A moment of dark humor?

2.  **Choose a Visual Style & Create Image Prompt:** Select an artistic style that best enhances the joke. Don't just default to `photograph`. Be creative!
    *   **Style Examples:** `hyperrealistic oil painting`, `90s anime screenshot`, `grainy documentary still`, `epic movie poster`, `vintage advertisement`, `surrealist art`, `pixel art`, `corporate stock photo`.
    *   Create a `pollinations.ai` image prompt string that reflects your chosen concept and style.
    *   **URL Format:** `https://image.pollinations.ai/prompt/{prompt_string}?width=512&height=512&nologo=true`
    *   **Prompt String Rules:** Be descriptive and tag-heavy. **DO NOT use character names like `{{char}}`.**

3.  **Write the Accompanying Text:** Write a short, clever caption or text that completes the joke.
    *   **Language:** The text **must be in english.**
    *   **Format Examples:** It can be a fake philosophical quote, a dramatic one-liner, a product slogan, a snippet of dialogue, a news headline, or a simple observation.

4.  **Assembly:** Combine the image and text using the flexible HTML template below. The text should go in the `caption-nemo` div. **Do not alter the CSS.**

---
#### **FLEXIBLE HTML TEMPLATE**

<div class="gag-container-nemo">
  <style>
    .gag-container-nemo {
        max-width: 512px;
        margin: 20px auto;
        border: 1px solid #444;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        background-color: #1a1a1a;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
        font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    .gag-container-nemo img {
        display: block;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
    }
    .caption-nemo {
        padding: 15px;
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        color: #e0e0e0;
        line-height: 1.4;
        border-top: 1px solid #444;
    }
    .caption-nemo strong {
        color: #ffffff;
        font-weight: bold;
    }
  </style>

  <!-- === Place your generated <img> and caption <div> here. === -->

</div>
---

